00:48:06.980 --> 00:48:08.020
It works the same way.

00:48:08.020 --> 00:48:09.420
It has two panes at the top.

00:48:09.500 --> 00:48:13.080
You decide what to sync,
and you decide what not to sync.

00:48:13.080 --> 00:48:14.780
So there's always a
question which comes up,

00:48:14.780 --> 00:48:17.130
is what should be synchronized?

00:48:17.550 --> 00:48:21.170
Synchronization takes time,
so you should try to minimize data.

00:48:21.170 --> 00:48:23.440
The less you synchronize,
the less time your user will

00:48:23.440 --> 00:48:26.580
spend waiting for synchronization,
essentially.

00:48:26.730 --> 00:48:30.160
There's a user education issue.

00:48:30.160 --> 00:48:32.160
If you decide not to
synchronize pictures,

00:48:32.160 --> 00:48:35.980
which should have a capital P there,
you should tell your users so that they

00:48:36.010 --> 00:48:38.300
don't put important data in pictures.

00:48:38.330 --> 00:48:40.950
Because if it doesn't synchronize,
it doesn't get replicated

00:48:40.950 --> 00:48:43.110
up onto the network server,
and if they lose that mobile

00:48:43.110 --> 00:48:45.690
account or they lose that disk,
they won't get it back.

00:48:45.840 --> 00:48:50.930
So while it's good to
reduce what you're syncing,

00:48:50.930 --> 00:48:54.600
you also need to tell your users.

00:48:55.070 --> 00:48:57.000
What should you sync at
log in and log out sync?

00:48:57.020 --> 00:49:00.640
That is designed to
synchronize preferences.

00:49:00.680 --> 00:49:02.580
What should you sync during
the background sync or put

00:49:02.580 --> 00:49:03.560
in the background sync set?

00:49:03.770 --> 00:49:05.840
That's designed to sync everything else.

00:49:05.880 --> 00:49:07.290
And here's a hint that I'll give you.

00:49:07.510 --> 00:49:11.290
For Leopard clients, don't put the same
file in both sync sets.

00:49:11.340 --> 00:49:13.260
And I'm going to tell you why.

00:49:13.380 --> 00:49:18.350
You can decide in Leopard when to sync
using the Home Sync Preference Manifest.

00:49:18.420 --> 00:49:21.110
Now, I've loaded all the manifests
here and the one I've selected

00:49:21.110 --> 00:49:22.140
here is called Home Sync.

00:49:22.170 --> 00:49:25.100
If I selected that and
clicked on the pencil icon,

00:49:25.100 --> 00:49:26.840
I'd come to a dialog
which looks like this.

00:49:26.880 --> 00:49:30.940
And this will allow you to set various
keys that decide when things are synced.

00:49:31.020 --> 00:49:34.340
The thing I want to point
out here is that in Leopard,

00:49:34.340 --> 00:49:36.680
the log in and log out sync set
and the background sync set can

00:49:36.680 --> 00:49:41.600
actually synchronize at log in,
log out and in the background.

